<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36205j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36205j">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36205j"> 205(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Just as I am</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Ku Kluxism.]</font> <font color="green">[At the initiation rite a neophyte]</font> is led to the sacred altar, &ldquo;where rests the American flag, upon which is a Holy Bible, open at the twelfth chapter of Romans, which Simmons says is his &lsquo;spiritual charter&rsquo;, and across the pages of the Word of God is a naked dagger;&rdquo; Then, says Fry, a parody on &ldquo;<mark>Just As I Am</mark>&rdquo; is sung &ldquo;by those of the elect who can carry a tune&rdquo;. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 270</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
